Name: dress-graph
Version: 0.5.0
Date: 2026-03-03
Author: Eduar Castrillo Velilla
Maintainer: Eduar Castrillo Velilla
Title: DRESS: A Continuous Framework for Structural Graph Refinement
Description: DRESS is a deterministic, parameter-free framework that
 iteratively refines the structural similarity of edges in a graph to produce
 a canonical fingerprint: a real-valued edge vector, obtained by converging a
 non-linear dynamical system to its unique fixed point. The fingerprint is
 isomorphism-invariant by construction, numerically stable (no overflow, no
 error amplification, no undefined behavior), fast and embarrassingly parallel to compute: DRESS total runtime
 is O(I * m * d_max) for I iterations to convergence, and convergence is
 guaranteed by Birkhoff contraction.
Categories: Graph Theory
Depends: octave (>= 5.0.0)
SystemRequirements: OpenMP (optional), CUDA Toolkit (optional, for GPU acceleration)
License: MIT
Url: https://github.com/velicast/dress-graph
